### 1. Get Products with Supplier details ($expand)
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Products?$expand=supplier

### 2. Get Sales Orders with Customer and Items ($expand)
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/SalesOrders?$expand=customer,items

### 3. Filter Products by price and sort by name ($filter & $orderby)
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Products?$filter=price gt 100&$orderby=name asc

### 4. Filter Customers by city ($filter)
GET http://localhost:4004/admin/Customers?$filter=city eq 'Mumbai'

### 5. Product Catalog View (Report with calculated stockStatus)
GET http://localhost:4004/report/ProductCatalog

### 6. Low Stock Alert (Report with filtered results)
GET http://localhost:4004/report/LowStockAlert

### 7. Order Report (Report with joined customer names)
GET http://localhost:4004/report/OrderReport

### 8. Sales Service restricted view (Verify field hiding)
GET http://localhost:4004/sales/Products

### 9. Deep Insert: Create Sales Order with Items (One deep insert POST)
POST http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "orderNumber": "SO-DEEP-777",
    "customer_ID": "cust1111-1234-4a5e-a1b2-c3d4e5f6g7h8",
    "orderDate": "2026-06-03",
    "amounts": 300.00,
    "currency_code": "USD",
    "status": "New",
    "items": [
        {
            "product_ID": "p3333333-1234-4a5e-a1b2-c3d4e5f6g7h8",
            "quantity": 10,
            "unitPrice": 25.00,
            "netAmount": 250.00
        },
        {
            "product_ID": "p6666666-1234-4a5e-a1b2-c3d4e5f6g7h8",
            "quantity": 1,
            "unitPrice": 50.00,
            "netAmount": 50.00
        }
    ]
}

### 10. Verify the deep insert was created correctly
GET http://localhost:4004/sales/SalesOrders?$filter=orderNumber eq 'SO-DEEP-777'&$expand=items

# ====================VALIDATION TESTS(Session-18)(6-6-26)===================================

@sales = http://localhost:4004/sales

### Test 1: Create order without customer (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    { "product_ID": "p1000001-...", "quantity": 2, "unitPrice": 50.00 }
  ]
}

### Test 2: Create order with past date (should fail)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "c1000001-...",
  "orderDate": "2020-01-01",
  "items": [
    { "product_ID": "p1000001-...", "quantity": 2, "unitPrice": 50.00 }
  ]
}

### Test 3: Create order with invalid item (quantity 0)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "c1000001-...",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "items": [
    { "product_ID": "p1000001-...", "quantity": 0, "unitPrice": 50.00 }
  ]
}

### Test 4: Create valid order (should succeed + auto-calculate totals!)
POST {{sales}}/SalesOrders
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "customer_ID": "c1000001-...",
  "orderNumber": "SO-201",
  "orderDate": "2026-06-15",
  "currency_code": "USD",
  "items": [
    { "product_ID": "p1000001-...", "quantity": 2, "unitPrice": 499.99 },
    { "product_ID": "p1000002-...", "quantity": 1, "unitPrice": 29.99 }
  ]
}

### Test 5: Try invalid status transition (New → Delivered should fail)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(ORDER-ID-FROM-TEST-4)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Delivered"
}

### Test 6: Valid status transition (New → Confirmed)
PATCH {{sales}}/SalesOrders(ORDER-ID-FROM-TEST-4)
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Confirmed"
}

